# Error Handling

- Runtime package errors should use `@alchemy/common` `BaseError` or a specific subclass.
- Do not throw plain `Error` in package runtime code; `.eslintrc` enforces this outside tests.
- Preserve `BaseError` docs URL and SDK version behavior when changing error classes.
- Do not import `BaseError` from `viem`; use `@alchemy/common`'s `BaseError`. An ESLint `no-restricted-imports` rule enforces this.
- Read `.agents/skills/error-handling/` before adding or refactoring errors.
